ernative frontier is developed through examining the phenomenological method of Martin Heidegger and the semiotic theory of Charles S. Peirce. While both of these thinkers independently provide great insight into the difficulty of accounting for human experience, this volume brings these insights into a new complementary synthesis. This synthesis opens new doors for understanding all aspects of conscious human experience, not just those that can be quantified, and without appealing to a mysterious spiritual principle.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aPhenomenology. 0aSemioticsxPhilosophy. 4aHeidegger. 4aPeirce. 4aPhänomenologie. 4aSemiotik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCharles Peirce.  aCognitive Semiotics.  aMartin Heidegger.  aPhenomenology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015050720 cprintz978150151433340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150517140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501505171423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501505171.jpg  a978-3-11-061030-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-074297-8  De Gruyter